The Course gives the students basic knowledge on different aspects of clinical infectious diseases, including diagnostics, treatment and prophylaxis together with elementary skills to handle patients with major infectious syndromes.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide contemporary knowledge and practical skills in the epidemiology, diagnosis, dIfferential diagnosis, treatment and prophylaxis of major infectious diseases.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the Course the student: 1. Knows biological etiological factors leading to pathological processes and their mechanisms of development. 2. Knows functional changes of the organism and their manifestations during infectious diseases. 3. Knows main possibilities of examination of infectious patient and diagnosis of infectious disease. 4. Knows principles of antibiotic treatment and immunopropylaxis. 5. Knows epidemiology of infectious diseases, risk factors and their management. 6. Is able to take history of infectious diseases. 7. Is able to examine the infectious patient, choose optimal diagnostic methods. 8. Is able to interpret the results of main diagnostic methods. 9. Is able to plan treatment strategies for major infectious syndromes.
